        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 6:23PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wildcat Hills State Recreation Area, or 12 miles south of
Scottsbluff, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minatare, Melbeta, McGrew, Wildcat Hills State Recreation Area,
Chimney Rock National Historic Site, and Wrights Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
